What does the following code print? (Assume `INT_MAX` is 2147483647 on this platform and signed overflow is UB — but consider what a naive mental model would predict.)

```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <climits>
int main() {
    std::string s = (sizeof(int) == 4) ? "32-bit int" : "other";
    std::cout << s << '\n';
}
```

The following program is intended to print `Hello` and flush the output, but it runs noticeably slower than expected in a tight loop. What is the bug?

```cpp
#include <iostream>
int main() {
    for (int i = 0; i < 100000; ++i) {
        std::cout << "Hello" << std::endl;
    }
}
```
